     Indentation blind
    ───────────────────
        / Part of a descriptor gap or divider segment.
        - A sequence of lines whose first non-space character (viz. not 20) is a no-break space (A0).
            : see `^^character identification$` @ `^^ Notes$`
        -
                                                ┌───╴◀────────┐
                           ┌─╴◀────┐            │             │
               start ┊     │       │            │   inline    │        ┊ end of
                of   ┊╶──┬─┴─╴‘ ’╶─┴─┬── A0 ──┬─┴─ character ─┴─┬────▶ ┊ line
